Diagnosis. Body length 4.0–5.5mm; frons dark brown, slightly open in male, narrowest part about 0.06 of head-width; face with silver pollinosity; antenna dark brown; postpedicel about 2.25 times as long as pedicel; scutum black with a light grey band in front of suture interrupted medially, and another grey band in front of scutellum; abdomen elongated, dark brown with grey pollinosity, syntergite 1+2 dark brown with grey margin; tergites 3 and 4 with lateral triangular dark brown marks, tergite 5 with a median mark (scutum and abdomen as in Fig. 1 of
Shinonaga et al. , 1991
).
